The article is about a presidential memorandum issued by Donald J. Trump on June 1, 2017. The memorandum is titled "Suspension of Limitations under the Jerusalem Embassy Act" and addresses the authority given to the President by the Constitution and laws of the United States. The memorandum states that the President has determined it necessary to suspend for a period of 6 months the limitations set forth in sections 3(b) and 7(b) of the Jerusalem Embassy Act of 1995 in order to protect the national security interests of the United States. The Secretary of State is directed to transmit the determination and accompanying report to Congress, and the determination will take effect after this transmission.